sols_latex:
The equation of the line is

\begin{align*}
\mathbf{x}=(1,1,0)+t(1,0,-2)
\end{align*}

where $\mathbf{x}=(x,y,z)$. We can write the line as three separate
equations

\begin{align*}
x&=1+t\\
y&=1\\
z&=-2t.
\end{align*}

If we use this for the equation of the plane, we get

\begin{align*}
x+y+z&=2\\
1+t+1-2t&=2\\
-t&=0
\end{align*}

and therefore we conclude that t=0. We plug this value of \emph{t} back
into the equation of the line to get that the point on the line that
intersects the plane is (1,1,0).

